720870f-a.title: Manhattan: Lenox Avenue - 134th Street
720870f-a.text:
Scene on Lenox Avenue looking north from 134th Street in the heart of the
Negro Colony, New York City.. Many of the buildings are owned and prac-
tically all are tenamted by colored residents.
1921 Paul Thompson, photographer
N.g. ~ LS04

715574f-a.title: Manhattan: 134th Street (West) - Lenox Avenue
715574f-a.text:
West 134th Street, west of Lenox Avenue, showing Harlem
living conditions. Several of the tenements on this
block have been demolished. 0thers are vacated and board-
ed up. The buildings individually shown are in this block
tho nearer to Seventh Avenue. Additional items of this
character are to be found in the pamphlet published by the
donor; '' Why Abandoned Buildings Should Be Demolished''.
About 1936
No's. -2-3-4
Gift of Committee on Housing

715576f-a.text:
